## Suggested Build Order

1. Spec 1 (recording & replay) Г?" substrate for everything.
2. Spec 3 (synthetic playtest) Г?" turns recording from "improve human bug reports" into "infinite autonomous bug discovery." Highest leverage.
3. Spec 8 (behavioral metrics) Г?" pairs with Spec 3 to define regressions for emergent behavior.
4. Spec 2 (game-side annotation UI) Г?" humans plug into the same system; game-specific work that can ship in parallel with Spec 4.
5. Spec 4 (standalone viewer) Г?" productivity multiplier for both agents and humans.
6. Spec 7 (corpus index) Г?" once corpus is large enough that browsing it linearly hurts.
7. Spec 9 (AI playtester) Г?" once Specs 3 and 8 are mature enough to drive qualitative feedback usefully.
8. Spec 5 (counterfactual) Г?" once concrete counterfactual queries emerge from agent workflows.
9. Spec 6 (strict-mode) Г?" independent, can ship at any point. Schedule based on determinism-bug pain.

